    "body": "While mining, the miner can choose to push the gas limit up by a bit, or to bring it down by a bit. The default behavior is that if blocks are full, the limit is pushed up, whereas it blocks are empty, the limit is pushed downwards towards a baseline. This baseline by default is 4.7M. You can change it with `--targetgaslimit` when starting your miner.",
